& \frac{2.272 \mathrm{~mol} \mathrm{C}}{2.272}=1 \\
& \frac{4.544 \mathrm{~mol} \mathrm{O}}{2.272}=2
\end{aligned}
$$

Since the resulting ratio is one carbon to two oxygen atoms, the empirical formula is $\mathrm{CO}_{2}$.

